HEADWORD: Dilleniaceae
<hw>Dilleniaceae</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a natural family of chiefly
tropical shrubs and trees and climbers having leathery leaves or
flattened leaflike stems, including the genera
<styp><gen>Dillenia</gen></styp> and
<styp><gen>Hibbertia</gen></styp>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> family <fam>Dilleniaceae</fam>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dilleniidae</ent>⟦br⟧
